content_snippet: @kenyaw @gdimeweather @Doc_Sanger Fujiwhara Effect is a fancy term for what happens when two cyclones get close enough that they "tug" on each other and influence each other's motion. It is neither good nor bad. That said, any hurricane is dangerous and I hope your relatives in the bayous stay safe.
content: @kenyaw @gdimeweather @Doc_Sanger Fujiwhara Effect is a fancy term for what happens when two cyclones get close enough that they "tug" on each other and influence each other's motion. It is neither good nor bad. That said, any hurricane is dangerous and I hope your relatives in the bayous stay safe.
